 countermeasures.
 (3)
     C.E. 3.3 FY2027 SE funding is in support of Intermediate-level and Depot-Level Maintenance standup for the IRST system for Phase III production unit procurements for I-Level ashore site standups at
 Lemoore and Iwakuni. Funds will prevent increased reliance on Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) for maintenance and repair of assets. Failure to resource will result in increased repair costs, repair
 cycle turnaround times, and the inability to repair IRST components on the aircraft carrier; all of which will significantly impact operational readiness of forward deployed IRST assets, particularly in a time of war.
 Without Intermediate and Depot level maintenance a significant increase in spares would be required to compensate for OEM repair capacity limits and maintain operational readiness. This cost is well in excess
 of the cost of building organic capacity on schedule. Support equipment funding is not strictly tied to fiscal year B-Kit procurement requirements and thus should not ramp similarly.




