INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L088$$, 2026, $$The WAR CONSUMABLES P-1 line item has two subcategories: Common Aircraft Armament Equipment (AAE) and Aerial Refueling Stores (ARS). The Common AAE program procures, modifies and upgrades
 Stores Suspension and Release Equipment (SSRE) which includes common bomb racks, peculiar bomb racks, missile launchers and related support for USN/USMC platforms. The ARS program procures,
 modifies, and upgrades aerial refueling stores, External Fuel Tanks (EFT) and related support.

 COMMON AIRCRAFT ARMAMENT EQUIPMENT (AAE)
 As directed by OPNAVINST 8000.16B (Naval Ordnance Maintenance Management Program (NOMMP)), the appropriation provides for procurement of new AAE to replace attrition losses, provides for production
 engineering support and satisfies commonality policy goals set forth by the Navy's Strike Warfare Master Plan. Specifically, the following equipment is funded as AAE within the War Consumables budget:
 - Upgrades, modifications and reliability improvements to common and peculiar bomb rack and associated equipment.
 - Upgrades, modifications and reliability improvements to various missile launchers and associated equipment that support the following platforms: F/A-18 A-F, EA-18G, AV-8B, AH-1W/Z, UH-1N/Y and MH-60R/
 S.
 - Upgrades, modifications and reliability improvements to Pure Air Generating Systems (PAGS). There are two variants of PAGS, Marotta Pure Air Compression Technology (MPACT)/High Pressure Pure Air
 Generators (HiPPAG), currently in use as on-board coolant generator for missile launchers carrying infrared (IR) seeking missiles.
 - The BRU-55 is an upgrade to the BRU-33 CVER (Canted Vertical), with electronic upgrades, which allows for the carriage and release of two MIL-STD-1760 weapons from a single F/A-18 A-F station. The
 BRU-55 was developed as part of the Mk-82 JDAM program.
 - A Universal Armament Interface (UAI) Type II interface is required for operation and carriage of the Small Diameter Bomb II (SDB II) weapon on the threshold aircrafts F-35B and F-35C and the objective aircraft
 F/A-18 E/F for the Department of the Navy (DoN). DoN will be using BRU-55 for carriage on F-18 E/F aircraft and BRU-61 for F-35 B/C to support the SDB II warfighter requirements, Initial Operating Capability
 (IOC), and schoolhouse requirements. BRU-55 A/A's will be modified to BRU-55 B/A's.
 - The BRU-61 pneumatic rack is required for carriage of SDB II on F-35 aircraft. The BRU-61 uses the Universal Armament Interface (UAI) software to pass updates from the aircraft to the weapon.
 - The Modular Common Launcher (MCL) is required for carriage of Precision Attack Strike Munition (PASM) on the AH-1Z aircraft. The MCL provides a platform for future integration of legacy weapons (e.g.
 Hellfire, JAGM, APKWS and unguided 2.75 in rockets) and emerging weapons (e.g. PASM, expanded APKWS and Air Launched Effects) on the AH-1Z, MH-60, and other platforms. MCL procurements will begin
 in FY 2029.

 AERIAL REFUELING STORES (ARS)$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
