INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L089$$, 2027, $$The Other Production Charges line provides funds for miscellaneous production support and testing services and instrumentation packages supporting tactical aircrew combat training to include TCTS II
 subsystems. The budget request supports the following efforts:

 TACTICAL COMBAT TRAINING SYSTEM (TCTS):
 The TCTS Increment II (TCTS II) program will procure fixed and transportable range equipment for the Navy to support shore-based aircrew training. TCTS II systems will transmit and track encrypted data from
 instrumented exercise participants and events, such as, weapons engagements, providing accurate, realistic, and timely feedback. TCTS II builds upon technology developed for existing tactical training range
 systems. Specifically, Link Inject To Live (LITL) provides constructive training information from ground based stations to live aircraft. Furthermore, F/A-18 Live, Virtual, Constructive (LVC) DRAGON will enhance
 the Airborne Electronic Attacks (AEA) LVC capability for Growler crews and F/A-18 pilots.

 TCTS II procurement primarily acquires airborne Participant Subsystems (PS) for F/A-18 and other tactical aircraft. TCTS II procures new PS to include Airborne Subsystem (AS) and Internal Mount (IM) to
 provide multiple independent levels of security (MILS) encryption capability for Fleet training exercises. The program will also procure Portable Support Equipment Subsystem (PSES).$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
