INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L072$$, 2026, $$This line item funds Safety / Obsolescence upgrades, Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) configuration updates, and Communication, Navigation, and Surveillance Air Traffic Management (CNS/ATM)
 modifications in support of FAA Next Generation Air Transportation System (NextGen) to the following cargo and transport aircraft: C-40A (QTY 19), C-20G (QTY 2), C-37A (QTY 1), C-37B (QTY 3), C-26D (QTY
 7), UC-35D (QTY 10), UC-12F (QTY 10), UC-12M (QTY 9), UC-12W (QTY 7), and UC-12W+ (QTY 2).

 The C-40A Clipper, C-20G Gulfstream IV, C-37A Gulfstream V, C-37B Gulfstream 550, and UC-35D Cessna Encore are commercial twin engine jet transport aircraft that provide time-critical medium lift logistic
 support for the fleet combatant commanders. The C-40A can accommodate 121 passengers, or 8 pallets of cargo, or a combination configuration of 3 pallets and 70 passengers with a range of 3,400 nautical
 miles. The C-20G can accommodate 26 passengers or 3 pallets of cargo, or a combination of pallets and passengers with a range of 5,100 nautical miles. The C-37 provides worldwide executive transport to
 Secretary of the Navy, Chief of Naval Operations, Commandant of the Marine Corps, and Fleet Commanders. The UC-35 provides transport for high priority passenger/cargo missions with time, place or mission
 sensitive requirements. The UC-35 can accommodate 7 passengers or 1,200 pounds of cargo with a range of 1,300 nautical miles. The UC-12 King Air and C-26 Metroliner variants are commercial twin turbo-
 prop aircraft that provide shorter-range light lift passenger/cargo transport and range control missions. The UC-12F/M is capable of carrying 8 passengers or maximum cargo capacity of 2,850 pounds, with a
 range of 1,075 nautical miles. The UC-12W and UC-12W+ are capable of carrying 9 passengers or a maximum capacity of 3,000 pounds with a range of 2,345 nautical miles. The C-26 is capable of carrying 19
 passengers 1,300 nautical miles.

 OSIP 071-86: Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) Configuration Updates Reserve Forces incorporates FAA mandates required for commercial aircraft.

 OSIP 012-04: Communication, Navigation and Surveillance - Air Traffic Management (CNS-ATM) updates are required to retain the Navy's capability to operate these aircraft worldwide.

 OSIP 013-16: Safety/Obsolescence Upgrades: Modifications support all readiness, obsolescence, and safety of flight improvements to existing Navy peculiar aircraft systems.

 FY27 modifications include the following:
 C-12F/M: High Frequency (HF) Radio.
 C-40A: Electronic Flight Bag Tablet Charging, Axle Upgrade, Heads Up Display (HUD), Mode 5 NRE, Display Electronic Upgrade (DEU) & Display Unit (DU) NRE, Flight Management Computer Upgrade.
 C-37A: Secure Communications Suite Operations (CSO), Enhanced Ground Proximity Warning (EGPWS) System, Radio Frequency Management (RFMU).
 C-37A/B: Starshield$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
