INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L086$$, 2026, $$Calibration Equipment Description:
 The objective of the Metrology/Calibration (METCAL) Program is to maintain required accuracy and consistency in Navy measurements. This ensures the required measurement accuracy of Test and
 Measurement Systems (TAMS) and Aviation Support Equipment (SE) used to test, repair and maintain Aviation Weapon Systems is adequate. Calibration is an on-cycle maintenance action and can be
 described as the comparison of a measurement device/system of unverified/unknown accuracy (TAMS or SE) to a device of known and greater accuracy (Calibration Standard).

 Fleet Readiness Centers (FRC) Support Equipment (SE)/Industrial Equipment Description:
 The Objective of the FRC SE/Industrial Equipment Investment program is to increase Ready Basic Aircraft (RBA). The purchase of equipment for the Fleet Readiness Centers will increase the agility, capability,
 and capacity to perform the critical mission of repair, overhaul of aircraft, engines, and components while maintaining the organic industrial capacity to meet current and future requirements.

 FY 2026 spend plan for FRCSE/Industrial Equipment (FIOP) includes $80,570 thousand of discretionary and $44,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $124,570 thousand.

 FY 2026 discretionary funding supports the procurement industrial equipment, peculiar and common ground support equipment, necessary to support aircraft, engine, and component depot level repairs. The
 mandatory funds provide advanced technology equipment including cold spray development and digital asset tracking.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
