INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1506_L084$$, 2026, $$All aviation spares requirements are developed using accredited sparing models. APN-6 is an "enabler" account that proactively supports the readiness and sustainment of Navy and Marine Corps aviation
 platforms by procuring all applicable spare and repair parts associated with end-items and modifications funded under APN Budget Activities (BA) 1-4 (aircraft), BA 5 (modification of aircraft), and BA 7 (aircraft
 support equipment and facilities). As an enabler account, APN-6 anticipates and aligns with program needs, installation schedules, basing strategies, and evolving maintenance data to ensure timely availability of
 critical components.

 The Initial spares category includes all repairable and consumable allowances required to support the quantity and Type/Model/Series (T/M/S) of aircraft and aircraft systems in new procurement. This includes
 support during Interim Contractor Support (ICS) for Repair of Repairables (ROR) prior to Material Support Date (MSD), as well as for aircraft modifications. Key platforms supported by initial spares include F-35,
 P-8A, MQ-25, CH-53K and KC-130J.

 Initial spares supporting aircraft procured under APN BA-1 through BA-4 are based on the number of aircraft being procured, basing plans, flying hours, maintenance data, and additional data elements derived
 from the Weapon System Planning Document and Aircraft Program Data File that are used as input parameters for the Readiness Based Sparing model and the Retail Inventory Model for Aviation for the
 determination of spare engine requirements. Spare engines and engine modules are procured under Initial spares during the production of the aircraft and do not transition to the Navy Working Capital Fund
 (NWCF).

 The Initial spares category funds Repair of Repairables (ROR) (9401) via contractor support, prior to the MSD, at which time repairs are turned over to the organic depots.

 Spares for Modification (9504) follow the APN BA-5 modification budget for all T/M/S supporting various Engineering Change Proposals (ECPs) and Operational Safety Improvement Program (OSIP) initiatives.

 Spares for Aircraft Support Equipment and Facilities follow the APN BA-7 budget for all T/M/S providing spares for training devices and support equipment (0720 and 9705-9709).

 Wholesale Supply Inventory (0930) includes spare parts that support long-term maintenance of weapon systems after they reach their Material Support Date (MSD). These spares help ensure system readiness
 and protect the financial health of the Navy Working Capital Fund (NWCF). They go beyond initial stock levels and include:

 Lay-In Spares - Purchased by the Program Office to build initial wholesale inventory, then transferred to NAVSUP WSS (WSS) for ongoing sustainment at MSD.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
