INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1507_L020$$, 2026, $$Multi-mission Affordable Capacity Effector (MACE) will provide launch platforms extended standoff capability, maximize weapon load-out, and control unit costs to rapidly scale production quantities and achieve
 necessary inventory levels. To control costs, maximize affordability, and extend capability relevance, MACE will leverage government directed interface standards and best commercial practices to enable the
 insertion of upgraded components or design changes to address obsolescence, producibility requirements, and enable rapid affordable future upgrades to pace the threat and meet key operational problems.

 In response to MACE requirements, the NAVAIR Rapid Capability Cell (NRCC) is utilizing Rapid Capability Office (RCO) authorities to accelerate the integration, test, and certification of the Hypersonic Weapon
 solution via Small Business Innovative Research (SBIR) competition for a low-cost air-launched hypersonic missile onto F/A-18E/F carrier-based aircraft. NRCC will broaden the competitive munitions industrial
 base to increase munitions production capacity, deliver relevant capability to the fleet ahead of adversary reaction times, demonstrate integration flexibility with rapidly iterating missile design through an Early
 Operational Capability (EOC) and provide the program structure necessary to enable transition into a Program of Record (POR) in accordance with acquisition transformation strategy. POR will continue testing
 thru Initial Operational Capability, a Full Rate Production Decision, and continued P3I enhancements to enable rapid affordable future upgrades to pace the threat and meet key operational problems.

 FY2027 MACE program includes includes $0 of discretionary funding and $156,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) funds for a total of $156,000 thousand FY2027 funding. FY2027 mandatory
 (reconciliation) funding supports the procurement of 353 LOT 1 MACE AURs and associated production engineering, logistics and program management support.

 FY2026 MACE program includes $0 of discretionary funding and $44,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) funds for a total of $44,000 thousand FY2026 funding. FY2026 mandatory (reconciliation) funding
 supports the Lot 1 AUR procurement.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
