 supports facilitization of capacity increases for GFE (Government Furnished Equipment) vendors supporting the Tomahawk Multi Year Procurement contract.

 The FY 2026 request for Industrial Preparedness includes $0 of discretionary and $190,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $190,000 thousand. FY 2026 total funding supports capacity
 investments at Raytheon and other sub-suppliers to support expanding overall production capacity up to 600 Tomahawk All Up Rounds per year. This investment is a pre-cursor to, and in support of, further
 expanding capacity on the Tomahawk production line up to 1,068 per year as part of the Tomahawk Multi Year Procurement contract.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
