 Description:
 The Navy's Patriot Advanced Capability 3 (PAC-3) Missile Segment Enhancement (MSE) is a high-velocity, hit-to-kill surface-to-air missile designed to intercept a wide range of threats, including tactical ballistic
 missiles, air-breathing threats, cruise missiles, and unmanned aerial systems. This capability builds upon the existing Army PAC-3 MSE by incorporating updated software and new radio communications,
 allowing the missile to be launched from MK 41 Vertical Launching Systems (VLS). The Navy PAC-3 MSE Integration into the Aegis Weapons System offers expanded battlespace performance against evolving
 threats.

 The FY 2027 request for PAC-3 MSE includes $97,835 thousand of discretionary and $1,632,988 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $1,730,823 thousand. The mandatory and discretionary
 funds are necessary to fully fund contract requirements for 405 PAC-3 MSE missiles and canisters (23 discretionary and 382 mandatory). Funding is also provided for engineering support and to resolve
 production Diminishing Manufacturing Sources.

 Other Related Budgets:
 RDTEN PE 0604307N PROJ 1447

 [P5 / PAC-3 MSE / Navy]: Both quantities and unit cost are estimates based on US Army contract pricing. Both quantities and unit cost will adjust based on award of DoN CLINs on ARMY contract in execution
 and final cost of the Navy canister.

 [P5 / Engineering Support]: Engineering Support, Government and Contractor, provided for both the DoN and US Army.




