INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1508_L006$$, 2026, $$Cartridge Actuated Devices/Propellant Actuated Devices (CAD/PAD) program's mission is to procure over 700 distinct service life-limited explosive/energetic devices. These devices perform critical safety
 functions in support of flight operations. Specifically, these devices are in US Navy's Naval Aircrew Common Ejection Seats (NACES), Aircraft safety of flight components, aircrew survival equipment and weapon
 systems release systems. The CAD/PAD yearly requirement is modeled on the total reported active aircraft as per the Office of the Naval Operations (OPNAV). The quantity for these unique requirements vary
 due to the distinct energetics of each CAD/PAD service life. Extending service life of CAD/PAD components beyond recommended use due to unavailability can pose a significant safety risk to aircrew. These
 explosives/energetics have finite service lives and are replaced during scheduled maintenance. Aircraft readiness may be impacted if any one of these items does not meet service life recommendations and
 cannot be extended. The new layout is listed below, by aircraft and description.

 T-6: Funding supports procurement of cartridge actuated and propellant actuated devices. Examples of items used on this aircraft include: Ejection seat catapult cartridges and rocket motors including Under
 Seat Rocket Motors, Impulse Cartridges, Digital Inline Timers, and Small-Column Insulated Delay initiators. Other aircraft cartridge actuated devices include Internal Canopy Mechanical Actuated Initiators, Seat
 Movement Mechanical Actuated Initiators, External Canopy Mechanical Actuated Initiators, Donor Assemblies, Manifolds, and ballistic transfer and canopy fracturing lines,

 T-38/F-5: Funding supports procurement of cartridge actuated and propellant actuated devices. Examples of items used on this aircraft include: Ejection seat catapult cartridges and rocket motors including
 Under Seat Rocket Motors, Impulse Cartridges, Digital Inline Timers, and Small-Column Insulated Delay initiators. Other aircraft cartridge actuated devices include Canopy removers and thrusters, and Donor
 Assemblies,

 V-22: Funding supports procurement of cartridge actuated devices. Examples of items used on this aircraft include: Internal Canopy Mechanical Actuated Initiators, External Canopy Mechanical Actuated
 Initiators, Gas Generators, Canopy and Hatch Shape Charge Assemblies, Thin Linear Explosive Ballistic Transfer Lines, Fire Extinguisher Cartridges, and Impulse Cartridges.

 F/A-18 & EA-18: Funding supports procurement of cartridge actuated and propellant actuated devices. Examples of items used on this aircraft include: Ejection seat cartridges and rocket motors including
 Parachute Deployment Rocket Motors, sequencer thermal batteries, Under Seat Rocket Motors, Impulse Cartridges, and seat catapult primary initiators, Digital Inline Timers, and Small-Column Insulated
 Delay initiators. Other aircraft devices include Fire Suppression Gas Generators, Fire Extinguisher Cartridges, ballistic transfer lines, canopy jettison rocket motors, DFIRS explosive doors, and DFIRS initiation
 components.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
