INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1611_L016$$, 2027, $$The Navy reached a comprehensive settlement to terminate the last four ships of the Constellation Class Frigate Program (FFG 64-67) with the prime contractor, Fincantieri Marinette Marine (FMM). While work
 continues on the first two ships, USS Constellation (FFG 62) and USS Congress (FFG 63), those ships remain under Navy review.

 No funds are requested for the procurement of new-built Constellation FFGs in FY26 and beyond. Funds appropriated in FY26 are exclusively for Frigate Industrial Base and Workforce development.

 The Guided Missile Frigate (FFG 62 Class) is a more lethal and survivable multi-mission small surface combatant. With the FFG 62 Class, the Navy will maximize the small surface combatant capabilities in the
 Anti-Surface Warfare (SUW), Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW), Electronic Warfare/Information Operations (EW/IO), Air Warfare (AW) mission areas, and survivability while keeping the ship affordable and as a
 part of a "high-low" mix of surface ships. The FFG 62 Class Capability Development Document was JROC approved in Feb 2019 and completed Milestone B, an informed Independent Cost Estimate, and award
 of the Detail Design & Construction contract in April 2020.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
