INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L005$$, 2027, $$The DDG Modernization (DDG MOD) Program is required to upgrade the in-service Flight I, II, and IIA DDG-51 Class ships in order to keep the DDG Class relevant and operational. The DDG MOD Program
 is composed of a series of improvements in both Hull, Mechanical, and Electrical (HM&E) and Combat Systems. Modernization changes are aligned with New Construction design to increase commonality and
 capitalize on Economic Order Quantities across all programs. Beginning in FY26, the program installs the next phase of combat capability enhancements, DDG MOD 2.0, bringing Integrated Air and Missile
 Defense (IAMD) capability to the DDG 51 Class. In addition to the DDG MOD 1.0 HM&E and Combat Systems upgrades, DDG MOD 2.0 ships will be equipped with SLQ-32(V)7 Surface Electronic Warfare
 Improvement Program (SEWIP) Block III (funded in 0204228N OPN 2312 AN/SLQ-32), SPY-6(V)4 Air and Missile Defense Radar (AMDR) with updated AEGIS Baseline 10M / Ballistic Missile Defense (BMD)
 6M, and High Efficiency Super-Capacity (HES-C) Chillers. DDG MOD 2.0 upgrades are planned for each ship's mid-life availability.

 Installation quantities starting in FY27 are as follows:
 DDG MOD 1.5: 1/0/0/0/0
 DDG MOD DMP2: 0/1/0/0/0
 DDG MOD 2.0: 0/0/2/2/2

 The definitions for DDG MOD installations are listed below:
 HM&E Modernization: HM&E
 DDG MOD 1.0: HM&E + C/S
 DDG MOD 1.5: HM&E + C/S + SLQ-32(V)7 (SLQ-32(V)7 is funded outside of DDG MOD 2.0)
 DDG MOD DMP2: SPY-6(V)4 + HES-C (these hulls have already received DDG MOD 1.5 in a previous availability)
 DDG MOD 2.0: HM&E + C/S + SLQ-32(V)7 + SPY-6(V)4 + HES-C

 HM&E modernization is comprised of Commercial Off the Shelf (COTS) technologies for Ship Control and Engineering Plant Control Systems. New systems provide increased situational awareness, reduce
 manpower workloads, and address reliability and obsolescence challenges with legacy systems.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
